$ Public Key Infrastructure
@ public key infrastructure

*Public Key Infrastructure* is abbreviated with PKI.

PKI is a system that allows to create, manage, distribute, use, store and revoke → development/security/cryptography/public-key/certificate[public key certificates].

{ TODO

  RFC 2585 → https://datatracker.ietf.org/doc/html/rfc2585#section-4[registered two MIME types] used for transfering certificates and CRLs:
    • `application/pkix-cert`
    • `application/pkix-crl`

  { PKIX

    As per RFC 2527, PKIX is an acronym for *Public Key Infrastructure (X.509)* (which is an IETF working group).

    → https://datatracker.ietf.org/wg/pkix/documents/[Documents] produced by the PKIX.

    The most significant usage of PKIX certificates is the authentication of domain names (= Domain Validation (DV) certificates).

  }

}

